HEADWORD: Myrtaceae
<hw>Myrtaceae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A natural family of trees
and shrubs yielding fragrant oils, including the myrtles, eucalyptus,
clove, allspice, and guava; the <altname>myrtle
family</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Myrtaceae</fam>, myrtle
family.</syn>⟦br⟧
